cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is about training deep neural networks using a modified version of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) that prioritizes elements of the training set with the largest novelty (error). This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses a deep neural network for its example, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the feedback loop used in the modified SGD process can be seen as a control system, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY).
